    narr:narration """This hub gathers accuracy assessments across the corpus's document types — memos, pitch decks, ADRs, call notes, and collective-memory entries — each judging factual precision, named-entity correctness, and citation discipline. Technical specs are checked for exactness: the [collective-memory assessment](narr:Assess_Accuracy_collective_memory) credits precise type definitions and accurate sequence diagrams, while the [code-memory assessment](narr:Assess_Accuracy_cm) notes precise type signatures and a SHACL schema. Pitch and GTM material is judged on quantified outcomes and named entities — the [investor pitch](narr:Assessment_Accuracy_1), [the customer's chief architect call](narr:Assessment_Accuracy_CustomerArchitect), and [GTM doc](narr:RubricAssess_Accuracy_GTM). Decision records ([ADR-001](narr:RubricAssess_Accuracy_ADR001), [ADR-002](narr:RubricAssess_Accuracy_ADR002)) are checked for cross-references and explicit status. The [Tony call](narr:RubricAssess_Accuracy_TonyCall) preserves dense dated numbers and verbatim quotes; the [Jan-7 GTM memory](narr:RubricAssess_Accuracy_20260107) and [IP-crisis](narr:Assessment_Accuracy_IPCrisis) entries foreground provenance and attribution. Recurring praise: verifiable claims, no false precision, consistent terminology.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#Assess_Accuracy_cm> ;
